{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase regulation of animal sales",
        "additional_details": "New regulations should include:\r\n \r\nAnimals to be sold through the breeder only, not through pet shops and third parties (this law currently only applies to cats and dogs)\r\n \r\nAll breeders to be licensed regardless of species or number of litters\r\n \r\nAdverts for stud animals to be banned\r\n \r\nAdverts for animal sales to be banned in the month prior to Christmas and the month prior to Easter\r\n \r\nAnimals must have had their recommended vaccinations before being sold",
        "background": "We believe that the legislation surrounding animal sales is insubstantial and should be changed to incorporate new requirements for breeders, and restrictions on sales and advertising of sales.",
